@*
    Example 2 — Persistence across reloads.

    Setting StorageKey makes the control write the chosen slug to
    localStorage on every apply, and read it back on first render. The
    resolution order is:

        Value > localStorage[StorageKey] > DefaultValue > "medium" > Sizes[0]

    so a returning visitor's stored choice always wins over DefaultValue.

    Note what is deliberately absent: there is no DetectFromSystem
    parameter here, unlike ThemeChooser and LocaleChooser. Browsers expose
    no "preferred text size" signal — there is no media query equivalent
    to prefers-color-scheme, and no navigator.languages analogue. Users
    who scale text at the OS level are served by browser zoom and the
    browser's own minimum-font-size, which this helper must not fight.

    The localStorage read happens inside OnAfterRenderAsync, so this is
    prerender-safe: static SSR renders the markup and simply skips the
    read.
*@

@page "/examples/text-size-chooser/persistence"
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@using LilyDesignSystem.Blazor.Helpers

<TextSizeChooser
    Label="Text size"
    Sizes="@Sizes"
    StorageKey="lily-text-size"
    DefaultValue="medium"
    OnChange="OnSizeChanged"
    @bind-Value="size" />

<p class="text-size-chooser-status" aria-live="polite">
    Text size: @(string.IsNullOrEmpty(size) ? "none" : TextSizeChooser.SizeName(size))
</p>

<p>Reload the page: the choice survives.</p>

@code {
    private static readonly string[] Sizes =
        new[] { "small", "medium", "large", "x-large", "xx-large" };

    private string size = "";

    // OnChange is for one-shot side effects — analytics, syncing the
    // choice to a user profile on the server, and so on. The DOM write
    // and the localStorage write have already happened by the time this
    // fires.
    private void OnSizeChanged(string slug)
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"text size applied: {slug}");
    }
}
